               <p>CHARLES HOBMAN. I am a <rs id="t18150510-83-viclabel498" type="occupation">wine-merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18150510-83-victim802 t18150510-83-viclabel498"></join>. On Tuesday, the 9th of May, I went up to dinner, and left the boots in the sample room, joining to the accounting-house; I heard a noise in the passage. The servant saw a man go out with a bundle; I pursued him, and waited at the Thames Police office till he came up; I opened his bundle, and found these boots; they are my property.</p>
               <p>
            
